cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.ROBOTS 

Reasoning: The paper discusses the problem of learning flexible models for multiple visual recognition tasks in a lightweight manner in the context of robot vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics) followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper focuses on visual perception tasks. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes a new benchmark for evaluating state-of-the-art algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.ROBOTS.
